# Implementation Plan - Owner's Analytics, DB Logic, and Export Refinement

This plan details the design and implementation steps to enhance the **Owner's Module** for Hontech AutoCenter Inc. It covers changing the database logic to persist completed jobs, building a dynamic daily/weekly/monthly analytics screen with Chart.js, and creating professionally styled PDF/Word exportable reports.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Storing Logic Change**: 
> Previously, jobs marked as `Completed` were deleted entirely from MongoDB, leaving no historical records. We will transition to keeping completed jobs in the database by setting their status to `Completed` and tracking the completion date (`dateCompleted`). 
> 
> To prevent active dashboard views (like TV mode and intake lists) from slowing down as completed jobs accumulate, we will update the primary `/api/jobs` query to exclude completed jobs. We will create a secure, dedicated `/api/jobs/analytics` endpoint for the owner to retrieve historical completed records for reports.

